WEBVTT

00:06.965 --> 00:08.705
[G ROANS]

00:23.773 --> 00:24.933
[PHONE RINGING]

00:51.718 --> 00:53.709
[CAR BEEPING]

01:20.205 --> 01:23.618
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

01:28.838 --> 01:29.827
Lois.

01:30.048 --> 01:32.380
[ROCK MUSIC CONTINUES]

01:49.275 --> 01:52.358
[COPY MACHINE BEEPING]

02:03.581 --> 02:05.196
Lois.

02:08.336 --> 02:10.372
Lois, are you okay?

03:14.861 --> 03:16.226
[CHATTER AND STATIC]

03:16.446 --> 03:18.653
WOMAN [ON RADIO]:
Extended outlook is sunny and beautiful.

03:18.865 --> 03:21.527
MAN [ON RADIO]:
This is a false alarm, apparently.

03:21.910 --> 03:24.071
WOMAN [ON RADIO]:
Metro 12-

03:25.997 --> 03:28.830
MAN [ON RADIO]: It's about, uh,
two days before and they still haven 't--

03:30.251 --> 03:33.209
Here, have this ﬁled for me by tonight.
Thanks.

03:34.005 --> 03:35.666
WOMAN:
Sure thing.

03:39.761 --> 03:42.298
Put away the pepper spray, Smallville.
It's only me.

03:42.847 --> 03:43.962
I wasn't hiding.

03:49.979 --> 03:52.686
Well, looks like
another thrilling Friday night.

03:52.899 --> 03:56.187
Just you and me ﬂying the redeye
on this paper airplane.

03:57.278 --> 04:01.396
-Almost like you never left the cockpit.
-Well, it's nice to have my copilot here.

04:04.452 --> 04:06.738
-What's with the bag?
-All-nighter survival kit.

04:08.331 --> 04:12.745
Comfort food, comfort footwear,
and comfort music.

04:12.961 --> 04:14.747
Chicken soup for my soul.

04:16.256 --> 04:17.962
Everything okay?

04:18.174 --> 04:19.914
You just seem a little off.

04:20.134 --> 04:23.001
The only thing I'm off
is a blurry butt-kicker's to-do list.

04:23.221 --> 04:24.711
Over a week and not so much as a:

04:24.931 --> 04:27.968
"Sorry, I've been busy saving the world,
but gotta run."

04:28.184 --> 04:31.676
I didn't realize the two of you
were actually seeing each other now.

04:32.272 --> 04:35.810
At this point it's not really seeing
so much as still looking...

04:36.025 --> 04:37.401
...but a girl's gotta hope.

04:38.319 --> 04:39.934
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

04:40.154 --> 04:41.940
LOIS:
Okay, get your engines going.

04:42.156 --> 04:44.989
Looks like there's a major ﬁre
on East Brunswick.

04:45.201 --> 04:47.192
If we're here all night, I'll get coffee.

04:47.704 --> 04:49.615
That's what I love about you,
Smallville.

04:49.831 --> 04:53.494
I say "ﬁre," you say "food."
I'll take mine black.

04:55.378 --> 04:56.834
That was quick.

04:57.880 --> 05:00.747
-Do you smell smoke?
-No.

05:06.514 --> 05:09.551
LOIS:
The ﬁre just got put out by the Blur.

05:10.143 --> 05:12.850
He is so amazing.
Here you and I are having a coffee...

05:13.062 --> 05:16.020
...while he's out squelching ﬁres
in three seconds ﬁat.

05:16.232 --> 05:17.688
Two seconds.

05:18.318 --> 05:20.479
-Not that anyone's counting.
-Yeah.

05:20.695 --> 05:21.684
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

05:21.904 --> 05:24.236
There's a high-speed motorcycle chase
out near the bypass.

05:24.449 --> 05:27.441
LOIS: Well, at least somebody's getting
a little action tonight.

05:32.165 --> 05:33.996
Clark, this is ice-cold.

05:34.208 --> 05:36.790
Never mind. I'll get it myself.

06:05.990 --> 06:07.696
Oliver.

06:07.992 --> 06:10.779
Is this your idea of fun,
now that you've hung up your bow?

06:10.995 --> 06:14.078
Should have known it was you.
Clark Kent, the king of buzz kill.

06:14.290 --> 06:16.622
You and your pet rock put on
a hell of a barbecue.

06:16.834 --> 06:18.745
But I had my money
on Doomsday, so....

06:18.961 --> 06:23.204
You can play it off as a joke, but I know
that the loss of Jimmy affected us both.

06:23.883 --> 06:26.625
Well, I guess God's got
a sick sense of humor.

06:26.844 --> 06:29.256
I'm sorry. I shouldn't be taking
your name in vain.

06:29.806 --> 06:31.967
What, you need to hear me say it?

06:33.643 --> 06:35.804
I should have listened to you.

06:36.312 --> 06:39.520
I should have gotten rid of Davis
instead of believing in him.

06:41.692 --> 06:43.603
It's a little late.

06:44.779 --> 06:47.942
I'm trying to make up for what happened,
not add to the casualty list.

06:48.157 --> 06:52.241
Well, I can't get my thrills leaping tall
buildings or outrunning speeding bullets.

06:52.453 --> 06:55.536
We mortals, we rely on a tweaked-out
Ducati and the open road.

06:55.915 --> 06:58.076
You're meant for more than this.
This isn't you.

06:58.292 --> 06:59.452
Who are you, huh?

07:00.711 --> 07:03.669
What's this? What's the S stand for?
What is that, "superstar"?

07:03.881 --> 07:05.792
It gives people hope.

07:06.008 --> 07:06.963
I'll tell you what, Clark.

07:07.176 --> 07:10.589
Why don't you, uh, go ahead and plaster
your symbol of superiority all over the city...

07:10.805 --> 07:13.137
...so people can worship you
like some kind of modern Jesus.

07:13.349 --> 07:16.216
That's what you want, right?
That's why you're here?

07:16.894 --> 07:18.885
-Here to save us.
-You need help.

07:19.856 --> 07:21.721
Maybe. But I hate to break it to you.

07:21.941 --> 07:24.648
Not everybody believes
in the second coming.

07:27.363 --> 07:28.978
[TIRES SQUEAL]

07:58.644 --> 07:59.679
[DOOR OPENS]

08:02.815 --> 08:04.351
TESS:
Have you found them?

08:04.734 --> 08:06.520
They should have reported in by now.

08:07.195 --> 08:08.935
They may have run into trouble.

08:13.951 --> 08:16.738
They didn't send out an SOS.

08:17.538 --> 08:21.622
And I should like to think that
12 ex-Navy SEALs could hold their own.

08:25.630 --> 08:28.542
The longer it takes for us to locate
these Kryptonians...

08:28.758 --> 08:30.919
...the more they'll blend in
and disappear.

08:31.135 --> 08:32.124
[G ROWLING]

08:32.345 --> 08:34.131
[GUNSHOTS AND MAN SCREAMING]

08:34.347 --> 08:36.429
[RAPID FOOTSTEPS OUTSIDE]

09:02.792 --> 09:05.704
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER COMM LINK]

09:12.426 --> 09:14.291
[KNOCKING]

09:37.326 --> 09:38.361
It's okay. It's just--

09:46.210 --> 09:48.451
[SCREAMS]

09:54.760 --> 09:56.842
[BUSY TONE]

09:57.346 --> 09:58.597
[PANTING AND WHIMPERING]

09:58.806 --> 10:00.842
[GROWLING NEARBY]

10:05.855 --> 10:07.470
[TESS SCREAMS]

10:57.531 --> 11:00.773
CLARK: This doesn't make any sense.
Tess is not the nervous-breakdown type.

11:00.993 --> 11:03.154
But she is the lying, cheating,
scheming type.

11:03.371 --> 11:05.862
You keep enough secrets,
they back up on your brain.

11:06.082 --> 11:09.040
Seriously, alien orb?
Now she's rambling about zombies?

11:09.251 --> 11:10.866
All adds up to "C for crazy."

11:11.087 --> 11:13.544
Just trust me.
There's more to the story than that.

11:13.756 --> 11:17.374
I respect how you got the lowdown
on Little Miss Lithium's mental break.

11:17.593 --> 11:20.175
-Sometimes you can be a little gullible.
-Really?

11:20.388 --> 11:23.050
Why don't you call your new friend
to weigh in on it?

11:23.265 --> 11:26.849
I'm not gonna cry wolf just
to get a pity call from Studly Do-Right.

11:27.061 --> 11:29.347
Something tells me
he'd side with me on this one, anyway.

11:29.563 --> 11:30.723
[LOIS CHUCKLES]

11:30.940 --> 11:34.603
Why? Because you have
so much in common?

11:35.611 --> 11:37.852
Dr. Coats. Maybe it's psychological.

11:38.072 --> 11:39.687
We could go with a Thorazine drip.

11:39.907 --> 11:42.398
No, the delusions are most likely caused
by the virus.

11:42.618 --> 11:44.950
We can't identify it,
and she's not responding to anti-virals.

11:45.162 --> 11:48.575
I want her isolated. I'm sending
all samples to the disease control labs.

11:48.791 --> 11:51.407
DOCTOR:
I'll get the samples ready for transport.

11:56.966 --> 11:58.752
Tess.

11:58.968 --> 12:01.584
Come on, Lois. Wait till she's awake
to get your comment.

12:01.804 --> 12:05.296
Don't you wanna ﬁnd out
what made Cruella snap?

12:09.812 --> 12:12.224
Tess, what happened to you?

12:12.648 --> 12:13.637
Care to comment?

12:15.484 --> 12:16.599
[TESS GROWLS]

12:16.819 --> 12:18.309
[LOIS GRUNTS]

12:20.489 --> 12:22.025
Tess?

12:24.368 --> 12:25.448
It's me, Clark.

12:26.537 --> 12:28.744
Doctor! Please, do something!

12:30.499 --> 12:32.285
Do something to help her now!

12:42.720 --> 12:45.632
Lois, are you okay?

12:47.475 --> 12:51.468
I've thrown down with Tess before,
but not quite like that.

12:52.021 --> 12:54.603
I think there may be some truth
in her story after all.

12:54.815 --> 12:58.683
Which is why I'm heading back
to the ofﬁce right now to write it.

12:59.820 --> 13:02.937
DOCTOR: Three mils per hour, push.
NURSE: Yes, doctor.

13:18.422 --> 13:20.959
Hey. Care for a little lo mein?

13:22.927 --> 13:25.634
| just came
from that Korean macrobiotic place.

13:25.846 --> 13:27.677
They do an exquisite kelp salad.

13:28.432 --> 13:33.426
I couldn't help noticing that you jumped
out of your chair when I came in here.

13:33.646 --> 13:35.853
I'd prefer if there were no secrets
between us.

13:36.065 --> 13:37.680
Then you're in the wrong business.

13:37.900 --> 13:38.889
[CH UCKLES]

13:39.276 --> 13:40.311
[DOOR OPENS]

13:40.945 --> 13:42.936
Chloe, I need your help.

13:43.155 --> 13:46.067
Can you run a blood test on this?
It belongs to Tess Mercer.

13:46.826 --> 13:48.282
She's infected with something.

13:48.494 --> 13:50.780
Lois and I went to see her.
She attacked us both.

13:50.996 --> 13:53.408
That's different than the way
she is every day, how?

13:53.624 --> 13:56.536
EMIL: We'll get right on it.
-l'm already in there.

13:59.547 --> 14:01.879
It looks like she had some visitors
this evening.

14:07.012 --> 14:08.673
And not the friendly kind.

14:09.390 --> 14:14.350
Viral rage can be traced to
a dysfunctional anterior singular cortex--

14:14.562 --> 14:18.146
The part of the brain that controls
the primitive ﬁght-or-ﬁight instinct.

14:21.652 --> 14:24.018
Well, the DCA site's
pretty impenetrable.

14:24.238 --> 14:27.230
That's okay. The Disease Control
Agency's sending a specialist.

14:27.449 --> 14:29.986
-Think you can get something out of him?
-I could try.

14:30.202 --> 14:32.944
It'll take me at least a half hour
to cross town.

14:34.707 --> 14:38.666
-Do you get motion sickness?
-Not really. Why do you ask?

14:41.422 --> 14:43.083
Really?

14:58.397 --> 15:00.763
Dr. Coats. Emil Hamilton.

15:01.150 --> 15:02.981
Has her condition changed at all?

15:03.193 --> 15:06.902
COATS: l'rn afraid not. And now the virus
has spread to 31 people and counting.

15:07.114 --> 15:10.356
EMIL: Any idea how the virus metastasized
so quickly throughout her body?

15:10.743 --> 15:13.359
Well, generally something spreading
this fast is airborne.

15:13.579 --> 15:17.117
We're about to quarantine the hospital,
send a team to Miss Mercer's ofﬁce.

15:17.458 --> 15:19.289
The Daily Planet?

15:19.501 --> 15:22.208
I thought Miss Mercer called an ambulance
from the Luthor mansion?

15:22.421 --> 15:26.164
No, she arrived at work experiencing
some type of a mental trauma.

15:26.550 --> 15:28.711
Paramedics picked her up at
the Daily Planet.

15:30.804 --> 15:32.465
Lois.

15:51.909 --> 15:53.570
LOIS:
Randall?

15:55.746 --> 15:57.282
Randall.

15:58.749 --> 16:01.661
Still sleeping on the job, I see.

16:01.877 --> 16:04.960
Rise and shine, Randall.
I've got a major news ﬂash for you.

16:07.091 --> 16:08.752
[G ROWLING]

16:33.951 --> 16:35.862
-C|ark.
-l'm gonna get you out of here.

16:36.078 --> 16:37.909
You have no idea
what you're up against.

16:38.122 --> 16:40.158
I'll get us through this.

16:53.846 --> 16:55.052
[LOIS YELLS]

17:19.288 --> 17:21.028
CLARK:
Are you okay?

17:27.838 --> 17:30.454
-You're hurt.
-l'm okay.

17:31.050 --> 17:32.460
Let's get you someplace safe.

17:51.737 --> 17:55.229
I know I was supposed to give this
to you after I checked your license...

17:55.449 --> 17:57.690
...but I couldn't help myself.

17:57.910 --> 17:59.446
A lot of platinum cards in here.

18:03.415 --> 18:06.077
But I bet this
is the most valuable one of all.

18:12.508 --> 18:13.998
Who is she?

18:14.218 --> 18:17.051
It's, uh-- Ahem.
She's just someone I used to know.

18:28.649 --> 18:29.764
POLICEWOMAN:
Hey, watch it.

18:29.983 --> 18:34.067
Just because I let that speeding ticket
slide doesn't mean you can speed in here.

18:34.279 --> 18:36.986
Well, I apologize, ofﬁcer. Don't shoot.

18:37.199 --> 18:41.784
But I've been up since, uh....
It's like 4:00, yeah, on Tuesday.

18:41.995 --> 18:45.704
So those pills right now are the only
thing keeping me vertical right now.

18:57.928 --> 19:00.135
It's ﬁne. Just leave it.

19:02.641 --> 19:05.974
-ls this a camera?
-Ha, ha. It's a what?

19:10.774 --> 19:13.265
It's some kind of spyware.

19:16.321 --> 19:18.357
Well, it's not mine.
I've never seen this.

19:18.657 --> 19:23.196
Right. And it just accidentally got caught
on your belt buckle?

19:23.412 --> 19:27.872
So you could, what? Plaster my butt
all over YouTube like Pamela Anderson?

19:28.917 --> 19:33.627
Okay, ﬁrst of all, no one's on YouTube
looking at Pamela Anderson's butt. Ha.

19:33.839 --> 19:36.000
Don't call or e-mail.

19:36.216 --> 19:37.501
Don't worry. I never do.

19:53.483 --> 19:55.269
Mercy.

20:07.247 --> 20:08.487
[SIGHS]

20:08.707 --> 20:11.915
Hey. I've isolated a suspect enzyme
from Tess' blood...

20:12.127 --> 20:15.164
...but I haven't been able to ﬁnd a match.
Anything from the DCA?

20:15.380 --> 20:19.464
Just that they think the virus is airborne
and deliberately released by someone.

20:19.676 --> 20:23.840
As you can see,
I created a model of the virus path.

20:26.225 --> 20:27.635
CHLOE:
Oh.

20:29.269 --> 20:33.012
Dr. Coats said the virus induces sleep
so that it can germinate.

20:33.232 --> 20:36.019
-If we could mimic the enzyme.
EMIL: We can create an antidote.

20:36.235 --> 20:39.727
We just need to ﬁnd
the right blood match.

20:40.906 --> 20:42.362
Huh.

20:42.574 --> 20:45.737
I only ever seen an enzyme like that
once before.

20:48.997 --> 20:50.328
In Davis Bloome.

21:15.732 --> 21:16.847
[SIRENS WAILING OUTSIDE]

21:19.778 --> 21:21.860
Do you think
they've quarantined the city?

21:22.072 --> 21:24.734
Probably. They found out
it was an airborne virus.

21:25.575 --> 21:28.191
You realize that means
we could both have it.

21:32.165 --> 21:34.326
We can't think like that.

21:36.128 --> 21:39.336
I'm just saying, once we go out there,
we might not make it.

21:39.965 --> 21:41.876
-Lois.
-l'm serious.

21:42.092 --> 21:43.502
Those things are everywhere.

21:45.053 --> 21:49.547
It would just suck to go out
without any closure.

21:52.352 --> 21:54.968
Clark, do you have
any deep, dark secrets?

21:57.566 --> 21:59.147
Do you?

22:03.196 --> 22:06.279
Last year, when I was talking
with the Red-Blue Blur...

22:07.993 --> 22:11.702
...for the ﬁrst time in my life,
I was doing something that mattered.

22:13.749 --> 22:17.742
And I wanted to work with him because
we did such good things together.

22:20.589 --> 22:23.251
But then I started to realize...

22:24.718 --> 22:27.676
...that I wasn'tjust doing it
to save people...

22:31.975 --> 22:34.307
...l was doing it for me.

22:40.192 --> 22:42.649
I just wanted to be with him.

22:46.990 --> 22:50.699
We all get crushes, Lois.
It doesn't make you a bad person.

22:51.870 --> 22:54.156
You don't understand.

22:56.083 --> 22:59.371
I had never had this connection
with someone before.

23:01.046 --> 23:05.756
Now that I have this connection, I don't
wanna go back to the way things were.

23:07.177 --> 23:09.463
This is embarrassing to admit.

23:15.894 --> 23:18.510
But I don't wanna be alone anymore.

23:28.323 --> 23:29.733
[PHONE RINGING]

23:36.289 --> 23:37.278
We gotta go.

23:37.499 --> 23:38.614
[ZOMBIE GROWLS]

23:38.834 --> 23:39.994
[SHOTGUN BLAST]

23:48.427 --> 23:51.043
Oliver? What are you doing here?

23:51.263 --> 23:53.800
Was looking for Tess when
the whole building went Resident Evil.

23:54.015 --> 23:55.141
[GROWLING NEARBY]

23:56.560 --> 23:57.675
Come on.

23:58.186 --> 24:01.303
OLIVER: Got any idea what triggered this
sudden appetite for human carpaccio?

24:01.523 --> 24:04.981
One minute, my copy editor's dozing,
next, he's trying to bite my face off.

24:05.193 --> 24:08.651
Same thing happened to Tess. When she
woke up she became one of them.

24:08.864 --> 24:10.775
You think this incubates
when people sleep.

24:10.991 --> 24:14.654
Hope not. We only have a few hours till
four million people get up to go to work.

24:14.870 --> 24:16.030
That's one hell of a rush hour.

24:16.246 --> 24:17.656
[ELEVATOR BELL RINGS]

24:17.873 --> 24:19.909
Get in here. You'll be safe.

24:22.252 --> 24:23.287
Clark.

24:23.753 --> 24:25.084
Someone's gotta go for help.

24:26.548 --> 24:28.163
Please, be careful.

24:29.593 --> 24:31.584
Everything's gonna be all right.

24:35.056 --> 24:36.887
Okay. Good luck, Clark.

24:37.309 --> 24:39.846
Oliver, she's in your hands now.

24:40.228 --> 24:42.139
Don't let her fall asleep.

24:49.988 --> 24:52.604
I found the antidote,
but we're running out of time.

24:52.824 --> 24:55.861
Where's this mystery, extraterrestrial
specimen with Davis Bloome's blood type?

24:56.077 --> 24:57.613
[SONIC BOOM]

24:57.829 --> 24:59.035
You're looking at him.

25:01.166 --> 25:02.622
Well, that explains a lot.

25:02.834 --> 25:05.325
How can you draw blood?
No needle can puncture my skin.

25:05.545 --> 25:10.665
Dr. Emil has a contact at LuthorCorp labs
who sent over some liquid kryptonite.

25:10.884 --> 25:14.342
We dip the needle in this
and it'll penetrate your skin.

25:22.437 --> 25:24.098
Here we go.

25:29.361 --> 25:31.602
[SCREAMS]

25:32.197 --> 25:33.812
The reaction's quite intense.

25:34.032 --> 25:36.364
-Get it out of him.
-No, no. We need more blood.

25:39.829 --> 25:41.035
-No.
-Almost there.

25:41.414 --> 25:42.665
CHLOE:
It's killing him.

25:44.417 --> 25:46.749
Good. He's gonna be okay, Chloe.

25:47.170 --> 25:49.502
His vitals are within range.

25:50.715 --> 25:54.924
-We need to get on that jet right now.
-No. I'm not leaving him here.

25:55.136 --> 25:57.343
I don't have time to prep the antidotes
by myself.

25:57.556 --> 26:00.093
Thousands, if not millions,
may be unknowingly affected.

26:00.308 --> 26:02.139
We have to get this
into the water supply.

26:02.352 --> 26:05.435
The sooner we do,
the more people we can reach.

26:23.999 --> 26:25.489
[SIGHS]

26:27.043 --> 26:28.544
LOIS:
God, Ollie.

26:30.380 --> 26:31.460
You're a mess.

26:33.300 --> 26:35.040
Yeah, I know.

26:47.022 --> 26:50.389
I'm sorry you have to see me
like this, Lois.

27:01.036 --> 27:03.027
Why don't you, um--?

27:03.580 --> 27:07.869
Why don't you go ahead and tell me
I'm full of it like you always used to, huh?

27:12.839 --> 27:14.795
God, I miss you.

27:17.218 --> 27:19.675
I miss our days together.

27:23.099 --> 27:26.216
Deep down in your heart,
I know you do too.

27:28.730 --> 27:30.891
Lois. Lois.

27:31.107 --> 27:34.065
Come on, hey. Lois. Hey, wake up.

27:34.861 --> 27:36.601
[G ROWLING]

27:48.208 --> 27:51.041
[LOIS YELLS]

27:55.924 --> 27:57.539
[G ROANS]

28:13.650 --> 28:15.641
[PHONE RINGING]

28:39.884 --> 28:41.920
EMIL: The antidote's permeated
the water supply...

28:42.137 --> 28:44.093
...and achieved
its target concentration.

28:44.305 --> 28:46.967
That's great for the people
taking a shower this morning.

28:47.183 --> 28:48.434
But what about the rest of us?

28:48.643 --> 28:50.383
[THUNDERCLAP]

28:50.603 --> 28:52.980
We're seeding the atmosphere
to release moisture.

28:53.314 --> 28:54.975
Deliver the virus a knockout blow.

28:55.483 --> 28:58.475
Should be able to create a curative
precipitation to blanket the city.

28:58.695 --> 29:02.813
PILOT [OVER PA]: We've reached
our target coordinates. Prepare to launch.

29:21.134 --> 29:23.295
In the event something goes wrong,
I want you to know...

29:23.511 --> 29:26.344
...your contributions
have been appreciated.

29:28.141 --> 29:30.473
Nothing's going wrong.

29:30.977 --> 29:33.138
Now I know why
Oliver had such faith in you.

29:33.354 --> 29:37.723
He ﬁnally met someone
who was a match for his conﬁdence.

29:38.818 --> 29:41.059
Probably no surprise
that you were the one to betray him.

29:41.696 --> 29:44.358
Are you gonna explain
that not-so-subtle barb?

29:44.574 --> 29:48.317
Well, you've been tracking Oliver
and the rest of his league, haven't you?

29:50.538 --> 29:54.201
Apparently, you've made yourself more
at home at Watchtower than I thought.

29:56.878 --> 29:58.539
May I ask why you're spying on him?

29:59.339 --> 30:02.331
The longer they stay separated,
the more vulnerable they are.

30:02.550 --> 30:06.042
-So you're protecting them?
-Yes. Someone has to.

30:06.262 --> 30:09.675
The people who are the worst
at taking care of themselves...

30:09.891 --> 30:13.383
...are the ones
the world actually needs the most.

30:13.603 --> 30:16.185
I assume that no one else knows this.

30:19.025 --> 30:21.107
No, it's my secret.

30:22.070 --> 30:24.903
Now the real question is,
will you keep it?

30:26.741 --> 30:28.902
Well, I guess
you'll just have to trust me.

30:32.747 --> 30:34.738
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

30:35.875 --> 30:37.786
[GROWLING NEARBY]

30:38.002 --> 30:39.993
[COPY MACHINE BEEPING]

30:40.755 --> 30:42.416
Lois.

30:45.260 --> 30:47.216
Lois, are you okay?

30:51.307 --> 30:52.922
Lois?

30:56.271 --> 30:57.761
Lois!

31:22.088 --> 31:23.419
[SCREAMING]

31:23.631 --> 31:26.122
It's okay. You're gonna be all right.

31:27.093 --> 31:28.958
[THUNDERCLAP]

32:17.226 --> 32:18.807
Lois?

32:20.730 --> 32:22.391
Clark.

32:22.607 --> 32:24.598
Clark, what happened?

32:25.860 --> 32:27.691
We made it.

33:10.655 --> 33:12.395
[SONIC BOOM]

33:16.828 --> 33:18.739
There we go.

33:19.539 --> 33:22.155
You only had to do one thing, Oliver...

33:22.500 --> 33:24.582
...keep her awake.

33:24.877 --> 33:27.254
But Lois almost died.

33:29.590 --> 33:32.798
You've spiraled down so far
you couldn't even protect her.

33:33.386 --> 33:36.844
Is there any part of the person
I used to know still there?

33:41.477 --> 33:43.263
Maybe not.

33:47.025 --> 33:49.687
Look, I understand
that it's hard trying to ﬁgure out...

33:49.902 --> 33:53.770
...how to come back from
what happened. Maybe you need help.

33:55.575 --> 33:59.568
Actually, I thought about
what you said...

34:03.041 --> 34:05.874
...and I took a look in the mirror
and you were right.

34:07.545 --> 34:10.958
I've been running away from myself
for a long time now.

34:16.637 --> 34:18.923
But now I know who I really am.

34:20.475 --> 34:22.932
All right. Then you know
what you have to do.

34:23.311 --> 34:24.721
Yeah.

34:34.155 --> 34:36.146
Thank you, Clark.

36:10.251 --> 36:11.741
Hey.

36:13.004 --> 36:14.039
Lois.

36:14.255 --> 36:16.712
Uh, I just came by to say thanks.

36:17.425 --> 36:21.464
And to apologize if I tried
to rip your head off or anything.

36:23.598 --> 36:26.715
You know, you have a pretty mean
left hook.

36:26.934 --> 36:29.095
I don't remember any of that.

36:31.564 --> 36:35.227
But I do remember seeing
a whole new side of Clark Kent.

36:35.776 --> 36:38.813
-Which side was that?
-l'll give you a hint.

36:40.323 --> 36:42.735
It starts with H and ends with "ero."

36:44.243 --> 36:46.825
I wasn't even wearing red or blue.

36:47.496 --> 36:50.033
You've got a long ways to go
before you can do that.

36:52.043 --> 36:54.204
Still, I think we make
a pretty good team.

36:55.463 --> 36:56.828
Yeah, we do.

36:59.800 --> 37:02.212
You never did tell me your secret.

37:03.971 --> 37:07.213
-We||....
-Relax, Smallville.

37:16.025 --> 37:17.981
Keep the mystery.

37:18.653 --> 37:21.565
You need to work
every last drop of it you've got.

37:45.721 --> 37:47.222
[PANTING]

38:20.172 --> 38:21.207
ZOD:
Coats.

38:24.135 --> 38:26.091
Three things cannot be long hidden.

38:28.556 --> 38:31.673
The sun, the moon...

38:32.935 --> 38:34.926
...and the truth.

38:39.608 --> 38:44.022
That's from a sacred human text,
from a prophet they call Buddha.

38:44.238 --> 38:46.194
-Major Zod—
-No.

38:53.497 --> 38:55.954
And the truth is...

38:57.418 --> 39:00.125
...you've become reckless,
haven't you?

39:00.338 --> 39:03.751
Unleashing a hostile virus to humanity.

39:12.475 --> 39:15.433
Have you lost your foresight?

39:16.103 --> 39:18.094
I did it all for our survival.

39:19.482 --> 39:23.942
Our cloak of anonymity is the only thing
keeping our presence from this world.

39:27.114 --> 39:32.450
They will hunt us
when they discover the virus' true origin.

39:33.245 --> 39:35.736
They won't have the chance, sir.

39:38.125 --> 39:40.958
I found the secret to our abilities
that were promised us.

39:41.170 --> 39:44.913
While you were rounding up our people,
I discovered one of us in Metropolis...

39:45.132 --> 39:46.633
...under our noses.

40:08.364 --> 40:10.355
Jor-El.

40:11.826 --> 40:13.657
He survived.

40:13.869 --> 40:16.451
Major, he didn't just survive.

40:16.664 --> 40:19.952
According to the news reports
of miraculous saves around the city...

40:20.167 --> 40:22.544
...he has power from the yellow sun.

40:23.421 --> 40:24.911
And yet we have none?

40:26.298 --> 40:31.543
He has chosen to harness the powers
for himself and left us defenseless.

40:32.847 --> 40:34.462
Jor-El betrayed us.

40:34.682 --> 40:38.595
Releasing the virus was the most
effective way to uncover him.

40:44.608 --> 40:46.018
Were you successful?

40:48.279 --> 40:51.487
His blood was used
to create the antidote to the virus.

40:51.699 --> 40:54.065
Track it. He's ours.

41:01.000 --> 41:02.956
I trust you see the risk was worth it.

41:04.628 --> 41:08.792
It takes a certain kind of man to step
outside the boundaries of his station.

41:12.261 --> 41:13.296
Kneel.

42:17.201 --> 42:19.192
[ENGLISH - US - SDH]
